The '''Bezirksoberliga Mittelfranken''' is currently the 7th tier of the [[German football league system]]. Until the introduction of the [[3rd Liga]] in 2008 it was the 6th tier of the league system. 

==Overview==

The [[Bezirksoberligen Bayern|Bezirksoberligas]] in [[Bavaria]] were introduced in [[1988]] to create a highest single-division playing level for each of the seven [[Bezirke]].

Before the introduction of the [[Bezirksoberligen Bayern|Bezirksoberligas]], the [[Bezirksklasse|Bezirksliga]] was the level of play below the Landesliga. The Bezirksliga Mittelfranken-Nord and Mittelfranken-S<U+00FC>d fed the Landesliga Bayern-Mitte as they now feed the Bezirksoberliga Mittelfranken.

The winner of the Bezirksoberliga Mittelfranken, like the winner of the [[Bezirksoberliga Niederbayern]] and [[Bezirksoberliga Oberpfalz]], is directly promoted to the [[Landesliga Bayern-Mitte]]. The second placed teams out of those leagues play-off for another promotion spot with the 15th placed team out of the Landesliga for the last spot there.However, in some years additional promotion places are available in the Landesliga.

The three bottom teams of the Bezirksoberliga are relegated to the Bezirksliga, the team just above those faces a play-off against the second placed Bezirksliga teams.

==Winners of Bezirksoberliga Mittelfranken==

 1989 TSV Weissenburg
 1990 TSV SW N<U+00FC>rnberg
 1991 BSC Erlangen
 1992 SC Schwabach 04
 1993 SG Quelle F<U+00FC>rth
 1994 ESV Rangierbahnhof N<U+00FC>rnberg
 1995 [[1. SC Feucht]]
 1996 ASV Neumarkt
 1997 SpVgg Ansbach
 1998 SpVgg Uehlfeld
 1999 TSV Neustadt/Aisch
 2000 [[SpVgg Greuther F<U+00FC>rth]] II
 2001 SC Eltersdorf
 2002 FV Wendelstein
 2003 1.FC Schnaittach
 2004 FSV Erlangen-Bruck
 2005 FV Wendelstein
 2006 SSV Jahn Forchheim
 2007 TSV Neustadt/Aisch
 2008 SV 73 N<U+00FC>rnberg S<U+00FC>d 

*With the ASV Neumarkt in 1996 the Bezirksoberliga Mittelfranken was won by a team from Oberpfalz.

==Teams promoted from Bezirksoberliga Mittelfranken to Landesliga Mitte via play-off games==

 1990 ASV Neumarkt
 1992 TSV Katzwang
 1994 ASV Vach
 1995 TSV Neustadt/Aisch
 1998 DJK Schwabach
 2001 ASV Zirndorf
 2004 SV Seligenporten
 2006 1.FC Schnaittach

